The paper deals with face hallucination, which is a computer vision problem related to image processing and computer graphics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new approach that incorporates contextual information and uses thresholding and reproducing learning techniques, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The paper also mentions the Small Sample Size (SSS) problem, which is related to information theory and statistical learning, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with image processing and reconstruction, which is related to multimedia and graphics, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
